14.  Qualifications. The Environment and Climate Change Law Expert and TA Project Manager 
must have: 

(i)  at  least  a  Master’s  degree  in  law  in  environment,  climate  change  and/or 
sustainable development; 
(ii)  at least 5 years of work experience as a law professor, lawyer or equivalent, 
preferably in the area of environment and/or climate change laws; 
(iii)  working  knowledge  of  current  environmental  and/or  climate  change  laws, 
sustainable development and related legal issues; 
(iv)  excellent  legal  research  and  writing,  communications  and  presentation  skills 
demonstrated by publications and experience speaking at environmental, climate 
change and/or sustainable development conferences; 
(v)  demonstrated project management experience, preferably in, capacity building 
programs; 
(vi)  demonstrated  ability  to  take  initiative  and  work  independently  with  minimal 
supervision; 
(vii)  excellent  interpersonal  skills  and  experience  working  in  a  multicultural 
environment; and 
(viii)  excellent oral and written communication skills in English. 

15.  Senior Project Coordinator (national, 3 person-months, intermittent)  

16.  Scope of Work. Under the supervision of ADB counsel, the Senior Project Coordinator will 
assist in the delivery of the in-person TTT programs and convening of the national and regional 
roundtables and assist with logistical arrangements and financial management and administration 
of TA-related activities.  

17.  Detailed Tasks. Under the supervision of ADB TA counsel, the project coordinator is 
expected to undertake the following tasks:  

(i)  provide logistical, financial management and administrative support for in-person 
TTT programs, national and regional roundtables and other TA-related events; 
(ii)  assist in obtaining the no-objection letters from the relevant DMCs;

